p.code: EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM users WHERE age > 18

div.p: The EXPLAIN command reveals the bytecode execution plan that the VDBE will execute. Each row represents one instruction with its operands and purpose. This transparency enables:
addr opcode p1 p2 p3 p4 comment

0 Init 0 10 0 Start at addr 10 1 OpenRead 0 2 0 3 Open table 'users' (3 cols) 2 Rewind 0 9 0 Position at first row 3 Column 0 1 1 Read 'age' column r1 4 Le 1 8 2 18 if age<=18 goto 8 5 Column 0 0 2 Read 'id' column r2 6 Column 0 2 3 Read 'name' column r3 7 ResultRow 2 2 0 Output r2, r3 (id, name) 8 Next 0 3 0 Advance cursor; loop to 3 9 Halt 0 0 0 End execution 10 Noop 0 0 0 (entry point)
